  "prompt": "What is the suggested people on my direct message?",
  "response": "The \"Suggested People\" in your direct messages (DMs) typically refers to a list of users that the platform's algorithm thinks you might want to message based on various factors. These factors can include:\n\n1. **Mutual Connections**: Users you both follow or are followed by.\n2. **Engagement**: Profiles you've interacted with recently (likes, comments, etc.).\n3. **Shared Interests**: Profiles with similar interests or content.\n4. **Location**: Users in your geographic area.\n5. **Activity**: Profiles that are active or have recently followed you.\n\nThe exact algorithm varies by platform (e.g., Instagram, Twitter, Facebook), but the goal is to make it easier for you to connect with people you might know or want to interact with. If you don't see any suggested people, it might be because the platform doesn't have enough data to make recommendations.\n\nLet me know if you need help with a specific platform!",
